  29 Mar 2007; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org>
  2005.1/ppc64/32bit-userland/packages,
  dev/ppc64/2007.0/32bit-userland/packages,
  ppc64/2006.0/32bit-userland/packages,
  ppc64/2006.1/32bit-userland/packages,
  ppc64/2007.0/32bit-userland/packages:
  Moved 32bit profiles from gcc-powerpc64 to kgcc64; bug #147126

  18 Mar 2007; Matti Bickel <mabi@gentoo.org> use.mask:
  afs usemask removed

  12 Feb 2007; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  dev/ppc32/2007.0/make.defaults,
  dev/ppc64/2007.0/32bit-userland/make.defaults,
  dev/ppc64/2007.0/64bit-userland/make.defaults,
  dev/ppc64/2007.0/multilib/make.defaults, ppc32/2006.0/make.defaults,
  ppc32/2006.1/make.defaults, ppc64/2006.0/32bit-userland/make.defaults,
  ppc64/2006.0/64bit-userland/make.defaults,
  ppc64/2006.0/multilib/make.defaults,
  ppc64/2006.1/32bit-userland/make.defaults,
  ppc64/2006.1/64bit-userland-gcc4/make.defaults,
  ppc64/2006.1/64bit-userland/make.defaults,
  ppc64/2006.1/multilib/make.defaults:
  Removed udev from default USE due to bug #158114.

  25 Jan 2007; Luca Barbato <lu_zero@gentoo.org> ppc32/2006.1/packages:
  remove unneeded constraint on gcc (fixes qemu)

  22 Jan 2007; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> use.mask:
  added lcd_devices_graphlcd to use.mask; bug #150925

  09 Jan 2007; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> 2005.1/ppc64/use.mask:
  removed afs; bug #160253

  09 Jan 2007; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> ppc64/virtuals:
  Nuked virtual/init, as it's killing new-style virtual deps; bug #159097

  04 Jan 2007; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> 1.0/use.mask,
  1.0_rc/use.mask, 1.2/use.mask, 1.4/use.mask, 2004.0/use.mask,
  2004.1/use.mask, 2004.2/use.mask, 2004.3/use.mask, 2005.0/use.mask,
  2005.1/ppc/use.mask, 2005.1/ppc64/use.mask, use.mask:
  Revert masking of PHP binary useflags.

  29 Dec 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> 1.0/use.mask,
  1.0_rc/use.mask, 1.2/use.mask, 1.4/use.mask, 2004.0/use.mask,
  2004.1/use.mask, 2004.2/use.mask, 2004.3/use.mask, 2005.0/use.mask,
  2005.1/ppc/use.mask, 2005.1/ppc64/use.mask, use.mask:
  Mask fdftk useflag on base profile and unmask for x86 only.

  16 Dec 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> +dev/ppc64/use.mask,
  +ppc64/use.mask:
  Added -ibm to use.mask on ppc64, since we're adding it to base/use.mask for
  bug #156000.

  07 Dec 2006; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> ppc32/2006.1/make.defaults:
  Added pdf as USE-flag, otherwise gtk2 will not build due to insufficient
  cairo-use-flags.

  07 Dec 2006; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org>:
  Starting with a ChangeLog as other arches already did.
